                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102H/327: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-12T14:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1919—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 12—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 2, 4 p.m., my June 20 [<hi rend="italic">21</hi>], 12 noon. American
                    firm in question is Standard Oil Company which today reports cannot further
                    delay action without losing site for which other interests are competing. They
                    request decision as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
